description: Project Structure
alwaysApply: true
---
- All content files must be located in the `content` directory.
- All CSS files must be located in the `css` directory.
- All JavaScript files must be located in the `javascript` directory.
- All template files must be located in the `templates` directory.
- For every HTML file in the `content` directory, there must be a matching Python (.py) file in the `source` directory.
- The matching Python file must be a superset of all code demonstrated in the corresponding content HTML file.
- templates + content generates a matching html file in the root at compile/runtime

